    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-09T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="792"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2111</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-09T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1915, 3 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 10, 12.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2861. Reported that <persName>Admiral Bachmann</persName>, Chief of Naval Staff,
                    and always at general headquarters with Emperor, and a <persName
                        corresp="#p_TAPFV1">Tirpitz</persName> man, has been replaced by
                        <persName>Admiral Holtzendorff</persName>. Latter has a brother who is
                    director of Hamburg-American Line and right-hand man of Ballin. Reported that
                        <persName corresp="#p_TAPFV1">Von Tirpitz</persName> angry at appointment of
                    Holtzendorff, and that last <hi rend="italic">Arabic</hi> note was a concession
                    to <persName corresp="#p_TAPFV1">Von Tirpitz</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von Jagow</persName> told me that his conversation with
                    me about <hi rend="italic">Arabic</hi>, reported in my 2777, August 25, 4 p.
                        m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d792fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, p.<ref target="#pg_526">526</ref>.</note> was
                    for consumption of American Government only and that he meant if possible to
                    keep it secret here, as public opinion here had to be considered. The <pb
                        facs="0801" n="543" xml:id="pg_543"/> whole matter is complicated with
                    internal politics and intrigues here and <persName corresp="#p_TAPFV1">Von
                        Tirpitz</persName> seems able to overrule Chancellor Emperor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
